Description:
Charming Family Home with Period Sophistication On 1880sqm (Approx)
SOLD PRIOR TO AUCTION | Exuding period character, this alluring residence is steeped in historic beauty. Elegantly enhanced throughout for added design and comfort, it has been beautifully attuned for family living, while still providing the privilege to stamp your own style.
~ Three double bedrooms, two with walk-in-robes and adjoining bathroom with walk-in shower.
~ Additional study with built-in desk and cabinetry.
~ Main bathroom with corner spa and spacious laundry.
~ From its beautiful streetscape with a circular driveway and porch, wander inside to witness the hallmarks of its era, featuring high ceilings, period decoration and sash windows.
~ The central kitchen is appointed with plenty of cupboard space, built-in dishwasher, double wall oven and induction cooktop.
~ Showcasing an idyllic entertainer's layout, a large free-flowing living, dining and kitchen seamlessly extend through glass French doors to a generous outdoor deck, framed by ornamental trees and manicured gardens.
~ Additional lounge is positioned at the front of the home with double sided fireplace for cosy evenings with your loved ones.
~ Climate-controlled by ducted heating and evaporative cooling.
~ 50,000lt inground water tank (triple filtered) servicing all taps + ozzie-kleen waste water recycle system.
~ Side access to a workshop with toilet and wash basin.
~ Further outdoor features include, horse shelter, feed/tack shed, 1,000lt water tank, garden shed, veggie patch, fruit trees and chook pen.
~ Within easy walking distance of transport, shops and adjacent to the recreation reserve with sporting ovals, heated outdoor swimming pool and tennis courts to enjoy year round.
While conveniently located close to everything on offer in this family-friendly suburb, this quiet setting feels like you're getting away from it all. Peace, privacy and the sounds of wildlife for company – what more do you need for a stress-free lifestyle?
Auction: Saturday, June 3rd 2017 at 1:30pm
Terms: 10% Deposit, Settlement 60 or 90 days. Vacant Possession.
Offers will be considered prior to Auction.

Description:
Large Family Home With High Investment Yield
Positioned just a short walk from Disney Street shops and set behind an idyllic white picket fence this pretty four bedroom treasure is a home of warmth and everlasting comfort. Recently updated, this homely heart warmer features two separate living areas, three double bedrooms (fitted BIRs), a fourth (master) bedroom with walk through robe and full ensuite, renovated second bathroom, large open plan kitchen including s/steel appliances and island bench, laundry and a large covered deck perfect for entertaining friends and family.
On an easy care block of 675sqm (approx) with side access from the neighboring laneway, this delightful haven enjoys a double carport and garden shed. Located within 1km of Crib Point Primary School, Reserve and local shops and under 1.5km from Cerberus Base and Golf Course, this home has endless options if you are looking to invest, enter the market or downsize. Please don't hesitate to contact us for more information.

Description:
MORTGAGEES AUCTION
Set in the Heart of Crib Point, an adorable three bedroom home on approx. 1000m2.
Ideal entry- level home, perfect for first home buyer or investor.
Offering huge potential with large sunken lounge, three spacious bedrooms all with built in robes, central bathroom with separate bath and shower, kitchen with Milano stainless steel appliances and ample cupboard & bench space, generous second living area opening onto full length verandah plus pergola for year round entertaining.
Outside features mature ornamental trees, a wide concrete drive way leading to double carport with through double gates into the magnificent back yard and grassed area perfect for the Big Shed, Caravan and Boat.
All set behind a secure high fence providing privacy yet within walking distance to Shops, Schools, Sporting facilities and Public transport. A lovely family home in need of a minor freshen up.
TERMS: 10% Deposit. Balance 30/60 Days. Vacant Possession.
Contact Exclusive Agent, Richard Whitehead on 0412 328 718 for further details.

Description:
Potenital Beyond Your Imagination
Situated on approx. 1113 sqm block this original house has all the right attributes to house a growing family whilst still having room to play.
With an abundance of space, privacy and convenience this home features 4 generous sized bedrooms with built in robes, master with built in robes and ensuite with double shower. Large L shaped lounge and dining area flowing through to the kitchen with access to the paved covered outdoor area with a built-in spa. Ample car accommodation with a 4-car carport, 4 car garage plus off street parking for an additional 4 cars. Features include gas wall heating, air conditioning, electric cooking, dishwasher and a wood burning fireplace in the garage.
A home in this position, only a few minutes' stroll to Crib Point village and Morradoo Station, won't last long.
For more information or to arrange your private viewing, please contact Jason Dowler anytime.
